Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician 12M - Elementary (35hrs) x 2 Burlington , ON Description POSITION: Permanent Library Technician x 2 35 hours/week, 12 months/yearSALARY CATEGORY: As per schedule (Level 4) - $21.42 per hourSTARTING DATE: Two Positions Available Start Date for Position 1: As Soon As PossibleStart Date for Position 2: July 4, 2023Position Summary:This position provides technical, administrative, and collection management services in multiple elementary school libraries. Elementary Library Technicians support the maintenance and use of library resources in various formats, model digital citizenship and lifelong learning skills, and demonstrate a growth mind-set in support of student learning.Duties &amp; Responsibilities: The successful candidate will provide each school library with specialized organizational skills and administrative support for the non-teaching tasks associated with the maintenance and use of library resources. The position links and processes resources within the library catalogue according to district-wide standards, promotes and assists with various library programs and services, and contributes to the growth and development of the library for 21st century learners.Qualifications:Completion and/or enrollment of a two (2) year certificate or diploma at a community college – Library &amp; Information Technician. The successful candidate must have strong organizational, communication and interpersonal skills as well as the ability to work both within a team environment and with minimal supervision. Applications, along with your resume and other supporting documents must be submitted through Apply to Education –https://hdsb.simplication.com/WLSBLogin.aspx by 4:00p.m. on Thursday June 1, 2023Job Code # 3506471 Compensation $21.42 per hour Closes: 1 June, 2023 Halton District School Board Burlington , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
