se selected for an interview will be contacted. St. Catharines Public Library is an equal opportunity employer committed to inclusive, barrier-free recruitment, selection processes, and work environments.COVID-19 vaccines are a requirement of the job unless you have an exemption on a medical or other protected ground pursuant to the Ontario Human Rights Code (OHRC). Please advise Human Resources to ensure your accommodation needs under the OHRC and Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act are provided through all stages of the recruitment process. Compensation $31.319 - $36.946 per hour (Pay Group 12, January 2021 FT schedule) plus $1.98 Pay Equity adjustment. All Union positions are currently under pay grid negotiations. Closes: 28 May, 2023 St. Catharines Public Library St Catharines , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
